ZH: 在与他人辩论时，攻心为上是不明智的。
EN: It is unwise to resort to attacking the heart when arguing with others.

ZH: 攻心为上会导致双方的关系破裂。
EN: Attacking the heart will only result in a broken relationship between both parties.

ZH: 必须以善意和理性对待他人，而不是攻心为上。
EN: We must treat others with goodwill and rationality, instead of resorting to attacking the heart.

ZH: 你不能仅仅通过攻心为上来解决问题。
EN: You cannot solve problems solely by attacking the heart.

ZH: 他是一个善良的人，从不采取攻心为上的方式对待他人。
EN: He is a kind person who never resorts to attacking the heart when dealing with others.

ZH: 请避免使用攻心为上的方法来解决分歧。
EN: Please avoid using the method of attacking the heart to resolve differences.

ZH: 在沟通中，攻心为上会使对方感到被伤害。
EN: Attacking the heart in communication will make the other party feel hurt.

ZH: 请放下攻心为上的态度，来尝试理性地交流。
EN: Please let go of the attitude of attacking the heart and try to communicate rationally.

ZH: 无论遇到什么情况，都不要轻易采取攻心为上的手段。
EN: No matter what the situation, do not resort to attacking the heart easily.

ZH: 在解决问题时，攻心为上只会增加矛盾。
EN: Attacking the heart when solving problems will only increase conflicts.

ZH: 攻心为上只会引起更多的误会和不满。
EN: Attacking the heart will only lead to more misunderstandings and dissatisfaction.

ZH: 我们应该尊重对方的感情，而不是攻心为上。
EN: We should respect the feelings of others, instead of attacking the heart.

ZH: 攻心为上并不能解决根本问题。
EN: Attacking the heart cannot solve the fundamental problem.

ZH: 遇到困难时，攻心为上只会让情况更糟。
EN: When facing difficulties, attacking the heart will only make the situation worse.

ZH: 攻心为上可以暂时伤害对方，但不会解决任何问题。
EN: Attacking the heart may temporarily hurt the other party, but it will not solve any problems.

ZH: 思想冲突时，攻心为上只会增加隔阂。
EN: When there is a conflict of ideas, attacking the heart will only increase alienation.

ZH: 攻心为上反映了对他人的不尊重。
EN: Attacking the heart reflects a lack of respect for others.

ZH: 要避免攻心为上，我们需要建立互相理解和尊重的关系。
EN: To avoid attacking the heart, we need to establish a relationship of mutual understanding and respect.

ZH: 攻心为上只会让双方陷入恶性循环。
EN: Attacking the heart will only make both parties fall into a vicious cycle.

ZH: 学会理性沟通，而不是以攻心为上的方式来解决分歧。
EN: Learn to communicate rationally, instead of resorting to attacking the heart to resolve differences.
